<!DOCTYPE html>

<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>Projects</title>
    <%- include('../partials/Header') %>
</head>
<body>
    <style>
        .projectContainer {
            border: 2px solid black;
            width: 250px;
            height: 250px;
            background-color: #add8e6;
            border-radius: 10%;
            margin-left: 5%;
            position: relative;
            display: inline-block;
        }

            .projectContainer:hover {
                background-color: #2f95a1;
                cursor: pointer;
                color: white;
            }

        .pTitle {
            text-align: center;
            color: black;
            font-size: 25px;
        }

        .pDescription {
            color: black;
            width: 90%;
            position: relative;
            left: 5%;
            height: 90%;
            overflow: auto;
        }

        a {
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        .pTag {
            position: absolute;
            right: 2%;
            bottom: 2%;
            color: #875d16;
            font-weight: bold;
            font-size: 15px;
        }

        .projectContainer:hover .pTag {
            color: #ffab1c;
        }
    </style>
    <%- include('../partials/navbar') %>
    <div class="w3-row-padding w3-padding-64 w3-container w3-light-grey">
        <h1>Projects</h1>
        <div class="projectContainer">
            <a href="/projects/distort">
                <div class="pTitle">
                    Photo distorter
                </div>
                <div class="pDescription">
                    This project arose from a bit of boredom mixed with a bit of creativity! After taking my Computer Graphics course, I became curious into the prospect of manipulating pixels. Thus this mini project was born. Copy and paste an image and apply affects! 
                </div>
                <div class="pTag">
                    JavaScript
                </div>
            </a>
        </div>

        <div class="projectContainer">
            <a href="/projects/distance">
                <div class="pTitle">
                    Distance calculator
                </div>
                <div class="pDescription">
                    This project searches state abbreviations using simple graph theory and calculates which depot should ship what, according to fairness and efficiency. This arose from a work meeting and was meant as a prototype.
                </div>
                <div class="pTag">
                    JavaScript, Prototype
                </div>
            </a>
        </div>

        <div class="projectContainer">
            <a href="/projects/game">
                <div class="pTitle">
                    Senior game
                </div>
                <div class="pDescription">
                    I created this little game in my senior year of highschool for a programming class. It's a basic game, but I just used canvas and no external libraries. 
                </div>
                <div class="pTag">
                    JavaScript, Game
                </div>
            </a>
        </div>

        <div class="projectContainer">
            <a href="/projects/gamble">
                <div class="pTitle">
                    Gambling simulator
                </div>
                <div class="pDescription">
                    This was created after my coworker <i>insisted</i> that he would be able to get lucky by gambling on horse races. I created a simulated environment and ran tests to see how many attempts it would take, and the odds of it happening.
                </div>
                <div class="pTag">
                    JavaScript
                </div>
            </a>
        </div> <br />

        <div class="projectContainer">
            <a href="/projects/graph">
                <div class="pTitle">
                    Graphing calculator
                </div>
                <div class="pDescription">
                    This project was created because it was I was on summer break and bored. I just finished calculus 2 and was interested in creating my own graphing calculator.
                </div>
                <div class="pTag">
                    JavaScript, Prototype
                </div>
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="w3-container w3-black w3-center w3-opacity w3-padding-64">
        <h1 class="w3-margin w3-xlarge">Quote of the decade: Strive for being nothing less than love</h1>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
